{{see|Tabernacle}}
==English==

===Etymology===
Old and modern French, from Latin ''[[tabernaculum]]'' "tent", "booth", "shed", from ''[[taberna]]'' "tavern"

===Noun===
'''tabernacle'''

# A [[dwelling-place]], especially that of [[God]].
# A [[canopy#Verb|canopied]] niche for holding an [[image]], [[statue]] or [[relic]].
# A temporary [[place]] of [[worship]].
# ''(nautical)'' The [[support]] for the [[heel]] of a [[mast]].
# The human body.
:*2 Corinthians 5:1-4 and 2 Peter 1:13-14 where the body is likened to the "tabernacle" used by the Israelite's wandering in the wilderness.

